# Popular Linux Distributions

A **Linux Distribution (Distro)** is a complete operating system built around the Linux kernel.

Some popular distributions include:

| Distribution | Common Use |
|--------------|------------|
| Ubuntu | Beginners, development, servers |
| Debian | Stable servers |
| Fedora | Latest technologies |
| CentOS Stream | Enterprise environments |
| Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) | Commercial enterprise servers |
| Amazon Linux | AWS EC2 instances |
| Kali Linux | Cybersecurity and penetration testing |
| Linux Mint | Desktop users |

