# Why Should DevOps Engineers Learn Linux?

Most production servers run Linux.

A DevOps engineer regularly:

- Connects to Linux servers using SSH
- Manages files and directories
- Installs software packages
- Monitors processes
- Configures services
- Writes shell scripts
- Automates deployments
- Troubleshoots server issues

Without Linux knowledge, working in DevOps is very difficult.

