# Basic Linux Terminology

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Kernel | Core of the operating system |
| Shell | Command-line interface used to interact with Linux |
| Terminal | Application used to access the shell |
| Distribution (Distro) | A version of Linux built around the Linux kernel |
| Root User | Administrator with full system access |
| File System | Method used to organize files and directories |
| Command | An instruction executed in the terminal |

