# Summary

- Linux is a free and open-source operating system.
- It was created by Linus Torvalds in 1991.
- The kernel is the core component of Linux.
- Linux is widely used in cloud computing, DevOps, web servers, cybersecurity, embedded systems, and software development.
- Most modern servers run Linux.
- Learning Linux is an essential first step toward becoming a DevOps Engineer or Cloud Engineer.

